- Install a CentOS on a VM.
- Let the network use dhcp


Login and do the follow:
- Disable firewalld
  systemctl disable firewalld

- Disable Postfix
  systemctl disable postfix

- Disable SELinux
  sed -i s/SELINUX=.*/SELINUX=disabled/ /etc/selinux/config

- Edit /etc/hosts
  echo "172.0.0.1 centos.localdomain centos" >> /etc/hosts

- Update the system
  yum upgrade -y

- Disable UseDNS on sshd
  echo "UseDNS no" >> /etc/ssh/sshd_config

- Install basic packages
  yum install -y net-tools bind-utils git open-vm-tools bash-completion bash-completion-extras vim-enhanced telnet nc wget

- Shutdown
  sync; halt

VCENTER:
- Poweroff the VM
- Disconnect the cd-rom and set to client device
- Convert it to template.
 
